			<div class="content" id="post-content-882671">
									

<p>The tone here is really off, and some of the writing is awkward enough to really bug me.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>For all intents and purposes a normal, unremarkable and simple green jade ring, SCP-714 has been shown to be able to expand and contract to fit any subject perfectly, though this is the least important of its properties.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The fact that that is not remotely clinical aside, this sentence roughly translates to</p>
<p><em>"this is a normal ring, a really normal ring that is normal, except that it isn't because it does something magical, and also it does other stuff."</em></p>
<p>…which doesn't even make sense.</p>

