														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2413499">
									

<p>Interesting. I was gonna say, &quot;I don't get it, why is this scary/horrible?&quot; Then I started reading the comments and realized this was an older skip from back when everything was still novel. Carry on! ^^</p>
<p>If you're seriously interested in a rewrite&#8230; start by asking yourself <em>why</em> the ring puts people to sleep. Who made it? Why did they make it? Is it functioning as-designed or has it gone wrong somehow? If the latter, why? What was it meant to do and why is it doing this other thing instead?</p>
<p>You don't need to put all of this into the skip, but you should privately know the answers before you begin reverse-engineering what the Foundation may or may not have learned about it.</p>
<p>The secret truth only you know should ideally be something horrible or baffling or even just incredible. Then you can hint at it all throughout the skip, leading the reader's imagination towards it but not quite saying it. Since the Foundation can't prove anything, and they're above rampant speculation. But we're not. And if you tell it right, we'll either figure out what you're hinting at&#8230; or else our imaginations will lead us somewhere even more horrible than what you'd planned.</p>
<p>Good luck! :D</p>

							</div>

								
					
